Prev_Next_Multiple
Write a C program to find the previous multiple & next multiple of 100 of a given three digit number using if-else. 
if the number is not 3 digit print invalid massage.

Sample input  : 234

Sample output : Previous multiple : 200
		                    next multiple : 300
Sample Input
234
Sample Output
Previous multiple : 200
next multiple : 300



  #include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int a;
    int pre,next;
    scanf("%d",&a);

    if(a <100 || a >=1000 ){
        printf("Invalid Input");
        return 0;
    }
    pre = a/100;
    next = 100 * (pre+1);
    pre = pre*100;
    
    printf("Previous multiple : %d\n",pre);
    printf("next multiple : %d", next);
    
}



